All I could say is that this app is a very good example of a Youtuber's life. The gameplay is amazing and I was so addicted to this game. The graphics, sound effects and background music are good enough. Initally at first I thought this game only has an average difficulty but it's at the later stage I realized the goals are not easy to achieve, so this game does present a bit of a fun challenge and annoying objectives. It's a bit laggy on my device but very playable with no crashes so far. Controls could have be better, I've hired people by mistake, took too long to get my collaboraters to uploads videos because I took quite a while to select him/her with the correct option and have quite some problems editing my videos. Some of the selectable buttons could be bigger. There are small bugs present in the game but easily solved by just returning to the main menu and loading my save. Overall, despite some of the negative impacts in this game and the mixed reviews from the PC version, it's still a very fun experience to learn the life of a Youtuber. It's worth the price for a portable mobile game. I would recommemd this game to anyone!
